<body><p>GE.<footnote name="1">9. To a large degree, prosecutions and the threat of prosecution have had a very limited 
impact on the number and level of human rights violations committed by State, guerrilla or 
paramilitary actors during the conflict. Most human rights violations remain in the 
preliminary stage of investigation. Law No. 975, known as &#8220;Justice and Peace Law&#8221;, on 
demobilized paramilitaries, appears to have served as a vehicle for truth, but not 
significantly as an instrument of criminal justice. In fact, almost all of the accused will most 
likely be released after eight years without ever having gone to trial.  
</footnote>4-10560 
